  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \"\u0b86\u0bb0\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\" \u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba3\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0b88\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd \u0baa\u0baf\u0ba3\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "\"On the Path of Health\" awareness tour in Yali",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The awareness drive \"On the path to health\" to be carried out by the Jaffna Arogya Nagar project will be held on the first day of August, Monday at 7 am.",
        "Jaffna. This two-wheeler journey will start from University Medical College and will reach Kokuvil Junction via Adiapadam Road, then reach Hospital Road via KKS Road and then reach Vembadi Junction via Av Road. From there it will reach Parameshwarach Junction via Palali Road and end at the entrance of Jaffna University Main Campus.",
        "This awareness rally, which is approximately 10 km long, will be held in Jaffna. University Vice-Chancellor Professor C. Sirisakunaraja, Dean of Faculty of Medicine Professor E. Surendra Kumaran, Jaffna. Municipal Chief Minister, Advocate V. Manivannan, Commissioner E.T. Jayaseelan, Director of Health Services, Northern Province Dr. Ketheeswaran, Jaffna. Director of Teaching Hospital Sathyamurthy, Jaffna. District Government President K. Maheson, Jaffna Divisional Secretary Ch. Sudarsan, Nallur Divisional Secretary Ms. Ezhilarasi Anran Yoganayagam and government officials, representatives of non-governmental organizations, university staff, students and school students will be attended by a large number of people.",
        "This awareness trip will be carried out under the project \"Jaffna Arogya Nagara\" which is being carried out under the auspices of the World Health Organization in order to create awareness among the public about health care. Organizers have requested all interested parties to attend the event.",
        "In many countries around the world, the World Bank has implemented the concept of \u201cHealthy Cities\u201d and identified significant healthy cities. On that basis Jaffna city is selected for the first time in South Asia and the project is being implemented.",
        "Jaffna. World Health Organization in Direct Coordination and Implementation of University Medical School, Department of Community and Family Medicine, Jaffna. City Council, UNICEF, Department of Health Services, Urban Development Authority, Ministry of Education, Government-Non-Government Organizations, Jaffna. It is noteworthy that various parties, including the District Government Chancellor, Jaffna and Nallur Divisional Secretaries, are providing their cooperation as partners of this project."
      ],
